@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place AlphaQuad where you want on
your system (hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc.). No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  You play by clicking on the tiles marked by a rotation arrow icon,
these are located between the letters. Each time you click on one of
these tiles, the letters around it will rotate clockwise by one
position. Here's an example:

    B   D       A   B
      *    -=>    *      Note: the '*' sign is the clicked tile.
    A   C       C   D

  Continue to move the lettered tiles until all the letters are at their
right places (all the letters are in white). When you finish the game,
AlphaQuad reshuffles the letters and you have a new game to solve...

  You can choose between 2 game board sizes, a 4 by 4 tiles board (with
the letters from A to P) or a 5 by 5 tiles board (with the letters from
A to Y).

  Have fun!

                                 OPTIONS

  In the game window, there are the following buttons:

 @{b}About@{ub}       - Displays the informations about the game.

 @{b}New Game@{ub}    - To restart the game.

 @{b}4 x 4/5 x 5@{ub} - Lets you choose the board size you want
               to play with.

